Ann Wauters scored 14 points and the
Cleveland Rockers used a 10-0 run in each half to beat Minnesota
58-48 Wednesday night, the Lynx's sixth straight loss.
article.headline: Lynx lose again in VanDerveer's debut
article.linkText: New head coach, same old story for woeful Lynx
article.story:
MINNEAPOLIS (AP) -- Ann Wauters scored 14 points and the Cleveland Rockers used a 10-0 run in each half to beat Minnesota 58-48 Wednesday night, the Lynx's sixth straight loss. The game was the first for former assistant Heidi VanDerveer, who replaced Brain Agler as coach of the Lynx on Tuesday. Agler resigned as coach but retained his position as general manager. "The last thing you want is to have to play on the road against a team that's emotionally charged,'' Cleveland coach Dan Hughes said. "It pleased me that when Minnesota did a good job of coming at us, we answered, and really stepped it up defensively a few times.'' Chasity Melvin added 13 points for the Rockers (8-12), while Tamara Moore had 14 points for the Lynx (6-14), who have lost 11 of 13. The Rockers touted being able to overcome Minnesota's emotional start with the new coach. "We just played the way our guy coaches and tried to take it inside to them as much as possible,'' Melvin said. "They have some great players who can shoot, so we tried to keep a hand in their faces at all times.'' Cleveland trailed 45-41 midway through the second half before scoring 10 straight points over a six-minute span to take the lead for good. Minnesota was held scoreless for the last 2:20 of the game while Cleveland hit seven of 10 free throws over the final two minutes. "We played 35 minutes of great basketball,'' Moore said. "If we play 40, we win. But we needed to make our own run in the last three minutes and couldn't do it.'' The teams traded leads 10 times before Cleveland went on a 10-0 run, holding Minnesota without a field goal for six minutes, to lead 23-15. The Lynx battled back behind two 3-pointers by Moore, but Cleveland maintained led 31-28 at halftime. "We were only down by three at the half, and I thought we did a lot of nice things in the first 20 minutes,'' VanDerveer said. "But the game is 40 minutes. Clearly we need to get rid of some of the silly fouls.'' Melvin finished with 12 rebounds for the Rockers. Game notes
Wednesday's game marked the start of VanDerveer's second stint as a midseason replacement head coach in the WNBA. She took over the Sacramento Monarchs with 13 games remaining in the 1997 season and led them to a 5-8 record. ... Wednesday's game concluded a season-long 15-day, five-game road trip for the Rockers. They went 2-3 on the trip, which took them to Charlotte, Indiana, Sacramento, Seattle and Minnesota. ... Despite their team's recent struggles, Minnesota's Katie Smith and Sevtlana Abrosimova remain the league's second-highest scoring combination. They entered Wednesday's game averaging a combined 32.0 points, which trailed only the 34.3 of Sheryl Swoopes and Tina Thompson of Houston.
